## Skill Implementation Notes

### Environment Variables

ExoMiner skill respects:

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `EXOMINER_HOME` | Path to ExoMiner repository root |
| `EXOMINER_MODELS` | Override model directory (default: `$EXOMINER_HOME/models`) |
| `EXOMINER_DATA` | Default data directory for light curves |
| `EXOMINER_OUTPUT` | Where results/reports are saved |
| `TF_CPP_MIN_LOG_LEVEL` | TensorFlow logging (set to `2` to suppress) |

Example:
```bash
export EXOMINER_HOME=/home/pi/ExoMiner
export EXOMINER_OUTPUT=/home/pi/exominer-results
```

### Data Flow

```
Light Curve FITS + TCE CSV
         ↓
  exominer preprocess (feature extraction)
         ↓
  Feature vector (200+ engineered features)
         ↓
  ExoMiner neural network inference
         ↓
  Classification score + explanation
         ↓
  Human-readable report
```

### Model Files

ExoMiner uses Keras `.h5` models located in `models/`:
- `exominer_Kepler.h5` — original Kepler model
- `exominer_TESS.h5` — TESS-adapted model
- `ExoMiner++_TESS.h5` — latest improved TESS model

Download from the [Zenodo repository](https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.15466292) if not included.

### Performance Notes

| Hardware | Inference time (per TCE) |
|----------|-------------------------|
| Laptop CPU (i7) | ~0.5 s |
| Pi 4 (4GB) | ~2-3 s |
| Pi Zero | ~8-12 s (model may need optimization) |

For Pi Zero: consider using quantized TensorFlow Lite models (`.tflite`) for faster inference.

