## Offline Usage Summary

| Component | Offline? | Data needed |
|-----------|----------|-------------|
| Model inference | ✅ Yes | Pre-trained `.h5` model file |
| Feature extraction | ✅ Yes | FITS light curve + TCE catalog |
| Model training | ✅ Yes | Labeled training set (FITS + CSV) |
| Data download | ❌ Requires internet | NASA archives (MAST, NExScI) |
| Model download | ❌ One-time | Zenodo or NASA servers |

**You only need internet to:**
1. Clone the repo and install Python packages (once)
2. Download pre-trained models (once) or training data (once)
3. Update to newest data releases (occasionally)

**After that: everything runs locally.**

